Findings: PA and lateral views of the chest show stability of the moderate right pleural effusion with complete collapse of right middle lobe and lower lobe. Right upper lobe and left lung are still clear. Median wires are related to sternotomy in patient with history of aortic valve replacement and are unchanged. Heart size is stable. There is no pneumothorax.
